ait time with any certainty, though.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:black\">Wait times depend on\nthe category of visa you’re asking for, the country you are from, how many\nother people from your country are asking for your type of visa, and the\nworkload at the immigration agencies. They can range from no time at all (as is\nsometimes the case for spouses and minor children of permanent residents) to 20\nyears (as is often the case for siblings of U.S. citizens who are Philippine\ncitizens).<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<ul type=\"disc\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:\n     Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi\">Family\n     First Preference (“F1”).</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto\">&nbsp;Unmarried adults, age 21 or older, who have at\n     least one U.S. citizen parent.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:\n     Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi\">Family\n     Second Preference: “F2A:”</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto\">&nbsp;Spouses and unmarried children of a green card\n     holder, so long as the children are younger than age 21.&nbsp;<strong>“F2B:”</strong>&nbsp;Unmarried\n     children aged 21 or older of a green card holder.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:\n     Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi\">Family\n     Third Preference (“F3”).</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto\">&nbsp;Married people, any age, who have at least one\n     U.S. citizen parent.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:\n     Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi\">Family\n     Fourth Preference (“F4”).</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto\">&nbsp;Sisters and brothers of U.S. citizens, where the\n     citizen is age 21 or older.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:black\">Owing to high demand,\nthe waits for people from China, India, Mexico, and the Philippines tend to be\nparticularly long.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<h2 style=\"margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;\nline-height:115%;font-family:Roboto;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt\">3.\nPreferred Employees and Workers, Mostly With U.S. Job Offers<o:p></o:p></span></h2>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:black\">A total of 140,000\ngreen cards are available each year to people whose job skills are needed in\nthe U.S. market. In most cases, a job offer is also required, and the employer\nmust prove that it has recruited for the job and not found any willing, able,\nqualified U.S. workers to hire instead of the immigrant. Because of annual\nlimits, this is a “preference category,” and some applicants wait years for an\navailable green card. Here are the subcategories:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\ncolor:black\">Employment First Preference.</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:black\">&nbsp;Priority workers,\nincluding:<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<ul type=\"disc\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto\">persons of extraordinary\n     ability in the arts, the sciences, education, business, or athletics<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto\">outstanding professors and\n     researchers, and<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto\">managers and executives of\n     multinational companies.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\ncolor:black\">Employment Second Preference.</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:black\">&nbsp;Professionals\nwith advanced degrees or exceptional ability.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\ncolor:black\">Employment Third Preference.</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:black\">&nbsp;Professionals and\nskilled or unskilled workers.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\ncolor:black\">Employment Fourth Preference.</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:black\">&nbsp;Religious workers\nand miscellaneous categories of workers and other “special immigrants”\n(described below).<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\ncolor:black\">Employment Fifth Preference.</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:black\">&nbsp;Investors willing\nto put $1 million into a U.S. business—or $500,000 if the business is in an\neconomically depressed area. The business must employ at least ten workers.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<h2 style=\"margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;\nline-height:115%;font-family:Roboto;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt\">4.\nAnnual Diversity Green Card Lottery<o:p></o:p></span></h2>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:black\">A certain number of\ngreen cards (currently 50,000) are made available to people from countries that\nin recent years have sent the fewest immigrants to the United States.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<h2 style=\"margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;\nline-height:115%;font-family:Roboto;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt\">5.\nSpecial Immigrants<o:p></o:p></span></h2>\n\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;color:black\">Occasionally, laws are\npassed making green cards available to people in special situations, such as\nyoung people under the care of a juvenile court, international broadcasters,\nand retired employees of the U.S. government abroad.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto\">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, 'parents', 'files/bxsMsQLWysyJr1PORqNRgejQY7PiqrNYsMZlP1Al.png', '#e5f6fd', 'files/F5nJ6DYq0VbXV1o3konQR4zo0XWtsfMUwe6ndZpp.png', NULL, '2023-06-16 04:35:28');
