(14, 4, 'Writ of Mandamus', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:27.0pt;\nfont-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\nRubik;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;mso-font-kerning:18.0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">Writ of Mandamus, Explained<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">A writ of mandamus is a\ncivil action lawsuit that seeks to compel a government entity to act in a\nspecific instance. It doesn’t mean you’ll win your case, but it does imply the\nagency must follow the law’s requirements. A lawsuit can be launched for non-immigrant\nor green card applications that have been handled incorrectly or denied, as\nwell as citizenship and adjustment of status applications that have been\ntreated similarly. You must establish that you have examined all other options\nwhen filing a petition for a writ of mandamus.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">A writ of mandamus is not\nthe same as an appeal. It requests that the higher court order the lower court\nto rule on a specific issue, but it does not instruct the judge on how to rule.\nIn an appeal, you would ask the higher court to rule that the trial court made\na mistake during the trial, such as admitting evidence improperly or giving\nincorrect jury instructions.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">When Can One File a Writ of Mandamus?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">The filing of a writ of\nmandamus has no time limit. A petition for a writ of mandamus, on the other\nhand, may be dismissed if you file it too late.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">When filing a petition for\na writ of mandamus, you must comply with Florida Rule of Appellate Procedure\n9.100. You must show all of the following:<o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">That you have a\n     clear right to relief<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">That there is\n     an undisputed duty on the lower court<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">That there is\n     no adequate remedy at law<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">That you asked\n     the lower court to act first<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">To compel the\n     lower court to rule on a motion, such as a post-conviction motion, that\n     was filed a long time ago, and no action was taken.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">To compel a\n     lower court to decide a case that was dismissed for lack of jurisdiction\n     in error.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">To compel the\n     release of records after a public records request was made.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">To compel a\n     court-appointed lawyer or public defender to provide information to you.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">To compel the\n     Department of Corrections to award you credit for time served.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Writ of Mandamus Elements<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">If you want to succeed in\na mandamus action, you must be able to establish three elements:<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:Roboto;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Roboto;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">1.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">The plaintiff has a clear\nright to the requested relief;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:Roboto;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Roboto;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">The agency has a clear\nduty to perform the act at issue; and<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:Roboto;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Roboto;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">There are no other\navailable adequate remedies.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Outcomes of Writs of Mandamus<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">A writ of mandamus lawsuit\nfiled in response to an unjustified delay could have a variety of outcomes.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Filing a writ of mandamus\nfrequently serves as a stern nudge to DHS. DHS may decide to adjudicate your\napplication and avoid the case entirely once the lawsuit is filed. The matter\nis closed if DHS decides before it has to respond to the lawsuit.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">In other cases, DHS will\npursue the writ of mandamus in court. DHS has 60 days to reply to the suit by\nsubmitting an answer or petition to dismiss. If you become disqualified for the\ndesired benefit as a result of the government’s unreasonable delay, the action\nmay be dismissed by a federal district court. If the judge finds that DHS took\nan undue amount of time to decide your application, the judge will order USCIS\nto make a decision in your case as soon as possible, usually within a certain\ntimeframe. A writ of mandamus should ideally encourage DHS and USCIS to approve\nyour pending immigration application as soon as possible. However, there’s a\ndanger that filing a writ of mandamus will result in your application being\ndenied quickly.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">While a writ of mandamus\ndoes not guarantee that your application will be successful, it can provide you\nwith peace of mind by ending a long and indefinite period of waiting.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Writ of Mandamus Limitations<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Only certain situations\nallow for the filing of a writ of mandamus. It can’t be used for any of the\nfollowing:<o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Request that an\n     incorrect lower court decision be reviewed by an appellate court.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Order the lower\n     court to take any action that is discretionary.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Control the\n     actions of a lower court.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Avoiding the\n     limitations imposed by the Florida constitution on the use of a writ of\n     mandamus.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto\">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, 'writ-of-mandamus', NULL, '#ffeed6', 'files/nbWfAmqjnRwzc3pmjn9kncvYbOVvjxHmwSn12X1A.png', NULL, '2023-06-16 04:36:48'),
(15, 4, 'Administrative Appeal', '<h1 style=\"margin-top: 0in; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:27.0pt;\nfont-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:\n-.3pt\">Administrative Appeal | Appealing an Immigration Decision<o:p></o:p></span></h1><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-fareast-theme-font:major-fareast;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:black\">Administrative Appeal</span></strong><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:black\">&nbsp;– A party that is displeased or unsatisfied with the outcome\nof a lawsuit for obvious reasons can file an appeal. If an immigrant’s\napplication to the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS)\nis denied, the judgment can be appealed to the Administrative Appeals Office\n(AAO). An appeal is an application, mostly in writing, to the authority to\nreview an unfavorable decision. Appeals can end in one of three outcomes: the\ninitial judgment may be reversed and dismissed, modified, or left\nunchanged.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:black\">Each administrative judgment in the context of immigration must\nfirst be appealed to a higher-level administrative agency, depending on the\ncase. The Board of Immigration Appeals (BIA) and the Administrative Appeals\nOffice (AAO), formerly known as the Administrative Appeals Unit, are the two\nprincipal administrative appellate authorities that supervise immigration\nappeals (AAU).<o:p></o:p></span></p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;\nfont-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:\n-.3pt\">Types of Immigration Appeals<o:p></o:p></span></h2><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:black\">Immigrants must go through a variety of appellate processes. These\nprocedures are determined by the immigrant’s petition or application, whether\nthe individual has valid immigration status, and whether the immigrant is\ndetained in an immigration detention facility.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:black\">There are five main types of immigration appeals:<o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Appeals\n     before the AAO;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Appeals\n     before the BIA;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Criminal\n     alien appeals;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Habeas\n     corpus, Mandamus and APA actions;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Petitions\n     for Review to U.S. Courts of Appeals;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Motion\n     to reconsider/motion to reopen.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;\nfont-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:\n-.3pt\">What types of immigration issues can be brought before the\nAdministrative Appeals Office?<o:p></o:p></span></h2><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:black\">The Administrative Appeals Office (AAO) examines decisions made by\nofficers of the United States Citizenship and Immigration Services (USCIS)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:black\">The AAO can hear appeals on around fifty various forms of\nimmigration applications and petitions, including:<o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Most\n     employment-based immigrant and non-immigrant visa petitions.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">EB-5\n     immigrant investor petitions.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Temporary\n     Protected Status applications.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">K-1\n     Fiancé(e) visa petitions.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Applications\n     for a waiver of inadmissibility.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Applications\n     for permission to reapply for admission after removal / deportation (I-212\n     waiver);<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Certain\n     special immigrant visa petitions.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Orphan\n     petitions.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">T\n     visa applications for victims of human trafficking and related adjustment\n     of status application.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">U\n     visa petitions for victims of criminal activity and related adjustment of\n     status application.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Applications\n     for certificates of naturalization and citizenship.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Applications\n     to preserve residence for naturalization purposes.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Immigration\n     and Customs Enforcement (ICE) determinations that a surety bond has been\n     breached.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;\nfont-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:\n-.3pt\">How to File an AAO Appeal?<o:p></o:p></span></h2><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:black\">When the USCIS declines an application, the agency sends the\napplicant a letter detailing why the application was denied. The letter will\ninclude instructions on how to file an appeal or a motion for reconsideration\nif the decision is one that can be challenged.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:black\">The majority of appeals must be filed using Form I-290B of the\nUnited States Customs and Immigration Service.<o:p></o:p></span></p><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;\nfont-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:\n-.3pt\">I-290B, Notice of Appeal or Motion<o:p></o:p></span></h2><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:black\">Use this form to file:<o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">An\n     appeal with the Administrative Appeals Office (AAO);&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">A\n     motion with the USCIS office that issued the latest decision in your case\n     (including a field office, service center, or the AAO); or<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Certain\n     appeals of the denial of an Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) Form\n     I-17, Petition for Approval of School for Attendance by Nonimmigrant\n     Student, with the ICE Student and Exchange Visitor Program.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><h3 style=\"margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size:18.0pt;\nline-height:115%;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#0B2051;\nletter-spacing:-.3pt\">You should not use this form if you:<o:p></o:p></span></h3><ul type=\"disc\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Are\n     the beneficiary of a petition. Generally, only an applicant or petitioner\n     may file an appeal or motion.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:black\">(NOTE: If you are the beneficiary of a Form I-140, Immigrant\nPetition for Alien Worker and USCIS will have revoked your approved Form I-140\nand advised you that you may file a motion or appeal. You may then file a Form\nI-290B. Please include the USCIS revocation notice with your Form I-290B)<o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\" style=\"margin-bottom: 1rem; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Want\n     to file an appeal with the Board of Immigration Appeals (BIA). Appeals of\n     Form I-130, Petition for Alien Relative, fall under the appellate\n     jurisdiction of the BIA. The BIA also has jurisdiction over appeals of\n     immigrant petitions that widow(er)s have filed using Form I-360, Petition\n     for Amerasian, Widow(er), or Special Immigrant. You may file an appeal\n     with the BIA using Form EOIR-29, Notice of Appeal to the Board of\n     Immigration Appeals.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Want\n     to appeal a USCIS “no risk” determination under the Adam Walsh Act. You\n     may seek further review by filing a motion to reopen or reconsider on Form\n     I-290B, Notice of Appeal or Motion, but there is no appeal available from\n     such a determination.&nbsp;&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Want\n     to appeal a Department of State consular officer’s denial of your U.S.\n     visa application (Forms DS-156, DS-156E, DS-156K, DS-117, DS-157, DS-230,\n     or DS-260). Please visit the Department of State website for information\n     about U.S. visa application denials.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; -webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial\">Want\n     to appeal a Special Agricultural Worker or Legalization application. You\n     must file these appeals on Form I-694, Notice of Appeal of Decision, Under\n     Sections 245A or 210 of the Immigration and Nationality Act.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><h2 style=\"margin-top: 0in; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; word-break: break-word;\"><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;\nfont-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:\n-.3pt\">Where Should I Put My Files?<o:p></o:p></span></h2><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:black\">Use the Direct Filing Addresses for Form I-290B, Notice of Appeal\nor Motion page to send your appeal or motion to the correct address.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 18.75pt; text-align: justify; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:black\">(If you or someone you know is looking for help with an\nimmigration appeal, we invite you to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://rajulaw.com/contact-us/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; transition: all 0.4s ease 0s; display: inline-block; box-shadow: none;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(162, 51, 56);\">contact us</span></a>&nbsp;for a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://rajulaw.com/appointment/\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"-webkit-tap-highlight-color: transparent; outline: 0px; transition: all 0.4s ease 0s; display: inline-block; box-shadow: none;\"><span style=\"color: rgb(162, 51, 56);\">free consultation</span></a>.)<o:p></o:p></span></p><p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto\">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, 'administrative-appeal', NULL, NULL, 'files/yKeFOX8Pp0A7kLriuYsETHm0snuiMjDrfeAnXMMV.png', NULL, '2023-06-16 04:36:50');
INSERT INTO `service_chield` (`id`, `service_id`, `name`, `desc`, `title`, `slag`, `image`, `color`, `icon`, `created_at`, `updated_at`) VALUES
(16, 4, 'Request For Evidence', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:27.0pt;\nfont-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\nRubik;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;mso-font-kerning:18.0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">What is Request For Evidence (RFE)?<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">You may receive a Request\nfor Further Evidence (RFE) from USCIS at the adjudication stage if you are\npreparing a US visa application and have previously filed your petition. An\nRFE, as the title suggests, is a request for additional documentation. It\nindicates that the USCIS officer examining your application requires additional\ninformation before deciding. An RFE does not guarantee that your application\nwill be denied, nor does it make it more likely to be rejected than if you had\nnot received the RFE.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">RFEs should:<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><ul type=\"disc\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Identify the\n     eligibility requirement(s) that have not been established and why the\n     evidence submitted is insufficient;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Identify any\n     missing evidence specifically required by the applicable statute,\n     regulation, or form instructions;<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Identify\n     examples of other evidence that may be submitted to establish eligibility;\n     and<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Request that\n     evidence.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">An officer should not\nrequest evidence outside the adjudication scope or otherwise irrelevant to an\nidentified deficiency. The RFE should ask for all the evidence the officer\nanticipates needing to determine eligibility and should clearly state the\ndeadline for response.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Avoiding Multiple RFEs<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">In some cases, the\nmaterial submitted in response to an RFE may highlight eligibility issues that\nthe officer missed during the first case review or lead to new lines of\ninvestigation. The officer may issue a follow-up RFE or NOID in this\ncircumstance. Officers should, however, include all of the material they expect\nto require to assess eligibility into a single RFE. Multiple RFEs are\nunnecessary since the officer carefully considers all of the apparent flaws in\nthe evidence.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Deadline for RFE<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">An RFE has a maximum\nresponse period of 12 weeks (84 days); officials are not permitted to allow\nadditional time to respond to an RFE.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">However, the laws allow\nUSCIS to give benefit requestors a variety of time frames to respond to an RFE.\nOfficers should adhere to conventional timetables to guarantee consistency.\nHowever, they may shorten response times on a case-by-case basis with\nsupervisory approval. Only when circumstances merit it, as judged by the\nofficer and supervisor, may this discretion be exercised.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">When an RFE is served by\nmail, the response is considered timely if it is received no more than three\ndays after the deadline, giving a total of 87 days for a reply to be made if\nUSCIS allows the maximum term of 84 days allowed by the regulations.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Benefit requestors\nresiding outside the United States or when USCIS mails an RFE from a foreign\nUSCIS field office will receive extended mailing time (14 days) as a matter of\npolicy.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">When relevant, the RFE\nshould mention the response deadline, including the extra days for postal RFEs.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto\">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, 'request-for-evidence', NULL, '#d6e6ff', 'files/r6VY7nn06T3QSmWoTn3wgG9x99Gttz43VA77fRIj.png', NULL, '2023-06-16 04:36:53'),
(17, 5, 'F-1 Visa', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:27.0pt;\nfont-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\nRubik;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;mso-font-kerning:18.0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">F-1: Academic Student<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">The USA has some of the\nbest universities in the world, and the student community and study\nopportunities are the most diverse here. Excellent quality of education,\nsophisticated educational programs, modern settings, and plentiful\npossibilities have made the USA one of the most desired destinations of study\nfor international students.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">International Students\nwill need to get an F-1 (non-immigrant visa) if they want to study in academic\ninstitutions in the USA. Visa holders of this category must complete their\neducational programs before their I-20 (Certificate of Eligibility for\nNonimmigrant Student Status) expires. I-20 is provided by the US College or\nUniversity showing that it has accepted the student, and the student can attend\nthe courses. International Students of both undergraduate and graduate programs\nmust need an active I-20&nbsp; to study in the USA.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">General Requirements for Admission<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Each academic institution\nin the United States has its unique admission standards. However, there are\nsome requirements that they all have in common. Both the international\nundergraduate and graduate students need to meet the following criteria\n(applicability varies) to get admission to US colleges and universities:<o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">High School\n     Diploma/ Degrees<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">A bachelor’s\n     degree if applying for a graduate program<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">English\n     proficiency test scores (TOEFL, IELTS, Duolingo Test)<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Transcripts of\n     previous academic records<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Motivation\n     letter/ Statement of Purpose/Admission Essay<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Letter of\n     Recommendations (LOR)<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Proof of\n     financial solvency (Bank Statement/ affidavit)<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">CV/Resume<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">SAT/ACT (for\n     Undergraduates)<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">GRE/GMAT/LSAT\n     (for graduates)<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Valid\n     International Passport<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Writing Sample\n     (for graduates)<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Admission Terms<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Colleges in the USA\nusually accept students in three intakes-&nbsp;<b>Fall</b>,&nbsp;<b>Spring</b>,\nand&nbsp;<b>Summer</b>. However, the highest numbers of international students\nare admitted to US colleges in the Fall intake. The fall admission decision\nprocess by the university usually starts in January and ends in April/ May,\ndepending on the programs. For the Spring session, the admission process\nusually begins in September, and the class starts in January.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Admission Process&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">The universities mention\nthe application deadlines on their websites well in advance so that the\nstudents can organize their applications and submit them on time. Early\napplications also stand a chance for various scholarships provided by\nuniversities or governments.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">All US universities and\ncolleges have an official website where students can submit their applications\nto the university application portals. They can also contact the\nuniversity/college admission office for any queries regarding their\napplication.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">After opening an account\nfor the application, students need to pay an application fee and submit the\naforementioned documents, which are the general admission requirements. Once\nstudents get admission, they need to collect their I-20 from the universities’\ninternational admission office and get an F1 visa to attend the classes.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">F1 Visa Application Process&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">To complete the F1 visa\napplication process, an international student goes through the following\nsteps:&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:Roboto;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Roboto;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">1.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Collect the admission\ndocuments/ I-20 from the admiting institution<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:Roboto;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Roboto;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">2.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Apply online for F-1 visa\nthrough the DS-160 form.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:Roboto;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Roboto;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">3.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Pay the Visa application\nfee.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:Roboto;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Roboto;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">4.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Pay the SEVIS I-901 fee.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:Roboto;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Roboto;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">5.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Schedule the F-1 visa\ninterview.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:Roboto;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Roboto;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">6.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Submit the file with the\nrequired F-1 visa documents.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left: 0.5in; text-align: justify; text-indent: -0.25in; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:Roboto;\nmso-bidi-font-family:Roboto;color:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:\nnone\">7.<span style=\"font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-variant-alternates: normal; font-kerning: auto; font-optical-sizing: auto; font-feature-settings: normal; font-variation-settings: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 7pt; line-height: normal; font-family: &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;\n</span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Attend the student/ F-1\nvisa interview.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">F1 Visa Requirements&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">The following documents\nare generally required to apply for an F-1 Visa:<o:p></o:p></span></p><ul type=\"disc\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">A valid\n     passport with at least 6 months of validity.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Form DS-160 for\n     non-immigrant visa applications.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Two photographs\n     meeting the US Visa Photo Requirements.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Proof of F-1\n     visa fee payment.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Form I-20. The\n     Form I-20 states the amount of funds that a student needs to finance the\n     education and live in the US for one academic year. The student must\n     submit documents that prove that the required funding for study is readily\n     available. This can be done by submitting various documents, such as:<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><ul type=\"disc\">\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Proof of\n     scholarship/ funding (if the student has already received the commitement\n     of funding from the university).<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Acceptance\n     letters of the student from the educational institution.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Bank\n     statements/ Bank Affidavit.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">If the student\n     is supported or sponsored by someone living in the US, the student will\n     have to submit form I-134, Affidavit of Support, and bank statements for\n     the last three years of the sponsor.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">If the student\n     is funding his/her US education through a loan, s/he must also show a\n     proof of the approved loan.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n <li class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"color: black; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;\n     font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:\n     &quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Documents that\n     prove the educational qualifications.<o:p></o:p></span></li>\n</ul><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><b><span style=\"font-size:22.5pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\nmso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;color:#0B2051;letter-spacing:-.3pt;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Tuition Waiver Opportunities:<o:p></o:p></span></b></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;\ncolor:black;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">International students\nneed to pay tuition and other fees every semester. The amount depends on the\nprogram, university, and location. Universities offer tuition waivers, fundings,\nscholarships, fellowships, and different assistantships like GA/TA/RA for\nstudents with desired profiles. A good IELTS Score, GRE/SAT Score, and SOP may\nhelp to secure such opportunities.&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p><p>\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n</p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto\">&nbsp;</span></p>', NULL, 'f-1-visa', NULL, '#d1ffdf', 'files/vOFn6w3EiA3daMW74wyVaId0lHdx1iMOYXF5zlqK.png', NULL, '2023-06-16 04:37:12'),
