(14, 8, 'Kaitlin Moran', 'Law Clerk', 'files/NF384jioIXWjVwzNH3BmXQztxRm1oPeJrEKT0aCN.png', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-style-textfill-fill-color:\n#404040;mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor:text1;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:\n100.0%;mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms:&quot;lumm=75000 lumo=25000&quot;;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">As a law firm, Rajulaw is pleased to\nhave Kaitlin Moran on staff. Kate Moran is a rising 3L at Lincoln Memorial\nUniversity’s Duncan School of Law. Raised in Tennessee, she pursued her\nundergraduate degree in Political Science and Government at the University of\nTennessee at Martin and went onto LMU for her legal education.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-style-textfill-fill-color:\n#404040;mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor:text1;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:\n100.0%;mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms:&quot;lumm=75000 lumo=25000&quot;;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">While in law school, Kate received her\nlimited license to practice on behalf of indigent clients through the Knox\nCounty Public Defender’s Community Law Office. Kate is also a member of the\nImmigration Law Society, the National Lawyers Guild, and the Women of Law\nSociety. Kate plans to pursue a career at the intersection of public interest\nimmigration law and criminal defense.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-style-textfill-fill-color:\n#404040;mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor:text1;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:\n100.0%;mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms:&quot;lumm=75000 lumo=25000&quot;;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Her passion for justice and commitment\nto her clients are evident in her exceptional legal skills and compassionate\nnature. At Rajulaw, we understand that navigating immigration law can be a\nchallenging process, but with Kate on your side, you can rest assured that your\ncase is in capable hands.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-style-textfill-fill-color:\n#404040;mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor:text1;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:\n100.0%;mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms:&quot;lumm=7500