(18, 10, 'Allison Pino, Esq.', 'Associate Attorney', 'files/eyE1eYS7mgbSKkOKPbODSJBBQEngssV7dvNid29N.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 14.4pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;\nmso-themetint:191;mso-style-textfill-fill-color:#404040;mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor:\ntext1;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms:\n&quot;lumm=75000 lumo=25000&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Allison Pino\nis a dedicated and compassionate immigration lawyer. Ms. Pino works at our\norganization as an Associate Attorney. She has a strong commitment to helping\nindividuals and families navigate the complex immigration system and achieve\ntheir dreams of living and working in the United States.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 14.4pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;\nmso-themetint:191;mso-style-textfill-fill-color:#404040;mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor:\ntext1;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms:\n&quot;lumm=75000 lumo=25000&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Allison holds\na Juris Doctor degree from the Stetson University College of Law, Florida, and\na Bachelor’s degree in Political Science and Government from the California\nState University Channel Islands. During her time at California State\nUniversity, she also participated in their “study abroad” program in political\nscience in Florence, Italy. The programs were focused on the development of\npolitical science and international relations. The courses are taught in both\nEnglish and Italian. California State University Channel Islands also honored\nher with a Mission Center Award for International Affairs for outstanding\nachievement in the field of international affairs. She has a deep understanding\nof immigration laws and regulations and a proven track record of successfully\nrepresenting clients in various immigration matters.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 14.4pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;color:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;\nmso-themetint:191;mso-style-textfill-fill-color:#404040;mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor:\ntext1;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms:\n&quot;lumm=75000 lumo=25000&quot;;mso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Throughout her\ncareer, Allison has successfully handled a wide range of immigration cases,\nincluding family-based visas, employment visas, asylum, and deportation\ndefense. She is known for her attention to detail, ability to effectively communicate\nwith clients, and strong negotiating skills.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"line-height: 14.4pt; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.0pt;font-family:Roboto;mso-fareast-font-family:\n&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bid