 cases from inception through trial, with a focus on litigation.\nShe has argued motions and received multiple jury verdicts within the New York\nState Supreme Court system. Her diligent research and thorough analysis of\nrelevant laws and regulations, combined with her Bachelor of Arts in English\nfrom the University at Albany, SUNY, has made her well-qualified to handle any\nnumber of immigration issues.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-style-textfill-fill-color:\n#404040;mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor:text1;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:\n100.0%;mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms:&quot;lumm=75000 lumo=25000&quot;;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Ms. Mazzotta has the legal knowledge\nand practical experience to take on challenging immigration cases. Her\nexperience as a teacher instilled in her a passion for assisting others and a\ndetermination to tailor her services to the specific requirements of each\nindividual client. As a legal advocate, she provides each of her clients with\nindividualized, sympathetic assistance as they navigate the complex immigration\nsystem. She is admitted to practice in New York State and in the United States\nDistrict Court for the Eastern and Southern Districts of New York.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family:Roboto;color:#404040;mso-themecolor:\ntext1;mso-themetint:191;mso-style-textfill-fill-color:#404040;mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor:\ntext1;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:100.0%;mso-style-textfill-fill-colo