(24, 7, 'Mac Murphy', 'Law Clerk', 'files/YMhtgUlhRRTR6bavKXpIYng0sate0XOeUrF3ftC2.jpg', '<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-style-textfill-fill-color:\n#404040;mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor:text1;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:\n100.0%;mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms:&quot;lumm=75000 lumo=25000&quot;;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Mac Murphy is a law clerk at Raju Law,\nan immigration law firm, where she works closely with clients to help them\nnavigate the complex immigration system. She received her bachelor’s degree in\ncriminal justice with a minor in sociology from La Salle University in 2021 and\nis currently pursuing her JD at Widener Delaware Law School, where she will\ngraduate in May of 2024. Mac is currently a member of the Moe Levine Trial Team\nat Delaware Law, where she participates in mock trials and closing summations.\nShe is also one of six members of the Pennsylvania Defense Clinic where she\nprovides pro-bono service to those who cannot afford private legal aid.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-style-textfill-fill-color:\n#404040;mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor:text1;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:\n100.0%;mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms:&quot;lumm=75000 lumo=25000&quot;;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">Mac is deeply invested in politics and\nthe justice system and has dedicated her career to advocating for those in\nneed. As a founding member and prior outreach coordinator of her family’s\nnon-profit, which is based in Philadelphia, PA, she has helped to provide\nhealthcare and support to underserved communities.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\nmso-fareast-font-family:&quot;Times New Roman&quot;;mso-bidi-font-family:Arial;\ncolor:#404040;mso-themecolor:text1;mso-themetint:191;mso-style-textfill-fill-color:\n#404040;mso-style-textfill-fill-themecolor:text1;mso-style-textfill-fill-alpha:\n100.0%;mso-style-textfill-fill-colortransforms:&quot;lumm=75000 lumo=25000&quot;;\nmso-font-kerning:0pt;mso-ligatures:none\">As the first person in her family to\ngraduate from college and pursue a law degree, Mac is passionate about breaking\ndown barriers and creating opportunities for others. Her personal connection to\nimmigration law, as the daughter of an immigrant, has inspired her to fight for\nthe rights of immigrants and ensure that they are treated fairly and justly.<o:p></o:p></span></p><p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-bottom: 18.75pt; text-align: justify; line-height: normal; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial;\"><span style=\"font-size:13.5pt;font-family:Roboto;\n